The MDT template expects the OTU table with \strong{OTU IDs in rows and sample IDs
in columns} (sequence read counts in the cells), and the sample and
taxonomy tables keyed by a leading \code{id} column. The reference sequences,
when available, are appended as a \code{DNA_sequence} column of the taxonomy file
(Darwin Core DNA-derived-data extension term).

When \code{check_dwc = TRUE} (the default), a lightweight Darwin Core compliance
check warns about recommended sample-level terms that are missing from
